    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Differentiation</title>
        <tabular bottom="medium" top="medium" left="medium" right="medium">
            <row header="yes">
                <cell>Student Group</cell>
                <cell>Strategy &amp; Learning Experience</cell>
            </row>
            <row>
                <cell>Struggling Learners (Support)</cell>
                <cell>Scaffolding: Provide step-by-step guides. Use color coding for characteristic (blue) and mantissa (green). Allow calculator verification. Focus on whole number characteristics first.</cell>
            </row>
            <row>
                <cell>On-Level Learners (Core)</cell>
                <cell>The core lesson activities as described above.</cell>
            </row>
            <row>
                <cell>Advanced Learners (Challenge)</cell>
                <cell>Extended Learning Experience: 1) Find <m>\text{antilog}(\bar{3}.7275)</m> — negative characteristic. 2) If <m>\log(x) = 2.5</m> and <m>\log(y) = 1.5</m>, find <m>xy</m> without finding <m>x</m> and <m>y</m> separately. 3) Solve: <m>10^{2x-1} = 500</m>. 4) Prove: <m>\text{antilog}(\log a + \log b) = ab</m>.</cell>
            </row>
        </tabular>
    </axiom>
    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Extended Learning Experience Solutions</title>
        <p xml:id="auto_ez9jvo60">
            <alert>1. <m>\text{antilog}(\bar{3}.7275)</m>:</alert>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_u8n98j85">
            <m>\bar{3}.7275</m> means <m>-3 + 0.7275</m>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_j4pdwih9">
            <m>\text{antilog}(0.7275) = 5.34</m>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_gri2tty5">
            <m>\text{antilog}(\bar{3}.7275) = 5.34 \times 10^{-3} = 0.00534</m>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_qxfvvw83">
            <alert>2. Finding <m>xy</m>:</alert>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_orhkkmyl">
            <m>\log(xy) = \log(x) + \log(y) = 2.5 + 1.5 = 4</m>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_68q1s20j">
            <m>xy = \text{antilog}(4) = 10^4 = 10{,}000</m>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_9767h783">
            <alert>3. Solving <m>10^{2x-1} = 500</m>:</alert>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_fqafrf6c">
            <m>2x - 1 = \log(500) = 2.699</m>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_wvkdk6p6">
            <m>2x = 3.699</m>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_1za8yeso">
            <m>x = 1.85</m>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_w5kntc3p">
            <alert>4. Proof:</alert>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_mccfur4r">
            <m>\text{antilog}(\log a + \log b) = \text{antilog}(\log(ab)) = ab</m>
        </p>
    </axiom>
    <xi:include href="../../resources-reflection.ptx"/>

</subsubsection>